# Invert: .gitignore everything, so invert what we want to NOT .gitignore
/*

# Standard Repo Files
!.gitignore
!.github/
!.github/**
# Belt-and-braces: re-ignore the public-mirror workflow's runtime
# artifact so it can never be accidentally committed from the source
# tree. The .github/** un-ignore above would otherwise make this
# generated file git-add-able. This negation must come AFTER that
# un-ignore — gitignore is last-match-wins (see issue #157 / PR #159).
.github/public-mirror/replacements.clean.txt
!/LICENSE
!/PATENTS
!/PRIOR_ART.md
!/README.md
!/.markdownlint.jsonc

# Claude config — whitelist shareable files, ignore everything else.
# New Claude-generated dirs (cache, sessions, projects, todos, ...) stay
# ignored by default. Add them to the allow-list explicitly if needed.
# Re-including a file inside an ignored dir requires un-ignoring each
# parent first (git's negation rule).
!/agents/
!/designs/
!/hooks/
!/memory/
!/output-styles/
!/plans/
!/rules/
!/skills/
!/CLAUDE.md
!/settings.json
!/keybindings.json

# Self-contained installer (and the payload dir #151 will populate).
# Each parent must be un-ignored before nested files become visible.
!/.global-claude-config/
!/.global-claude-config/**

# Per-repo config for /issue-address and friends. Lives in the
# *nested* .claude/ (this repo's root IS ~/.claude, so .claude/ here
# is the per-repo config for using ~/.claude on itself). Each parent
# must be un-ignored before the file becomes visible to git.
!/.claude/
!/.claude/rules/
!/.claude/rules/repo-config.md

# Always ignore local/temp/backup/lock files anywhere under .claude/,
# even inside whitelisted directories
/**/*.local.*
/**/*.backup.*
/**/*.lock
/**/tmp/
/**/worktrees/

# Repo-root CLAUDE override files (sibling to CLAUDE.md)
/CLAUDE.local.*

# Backup files from Claude setup
*.backup.*

#
# Below this should be excluded, but it is belt-and-braces
#

# macOS Finder metadata and temp dirs
.DS_Store
__MACOSX/

# macOS system files
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride
Icon
._*

# Git repo metadata
.git/

# Misc
*.log
*.tmp

#VSCode swapfile
*.swp

